# Cursor Rules for Broqui Bot Next

## Project Patterns
- Next.js 15 App Router architecture with server and client components
- Firebase Authentication for user management
- OpenAI API integration for chat functionality
- Image upload and analysis capabilities
- Food-specific AI assistant constraint pattern

## Implementation Preferences
- TypeScript for all components and functions
- Tailwind CSS for styling with shadcn/ui component library
- Server components by default, client components when necessary
- React hooks for shared logic
- Focused, single-responsibility components
- Proper error handling throughout the application
- Accessibility-first approach to UI development

## Critical Paths
- Authentication flow with Firebase
- Chat messaging system with OpenAI integration
- Image upload and processing workflow
- Response streaming from OpenAI API
- Topic constraint enforcement for food-only responses

## Known Challenges
- Ensuring AI responses stay on food-related topics
- Optimizing image uploads for efficient processing
- Managing OpenAI API costs
- Ensuring responsive design works well on all devices
- Firebase authentication and protected routes implementation

## Evolution Notes
- Project is in initial planning phase
- Memory bank established to guide development
- Implementation will proceed in phases

## Tool Usage
- Next.js 15 with App Router for routing and pages
- Firebase for authentication and storage
- OpenAI GPT-4 and Vision API for AI capabilities
- Tailwind CSS and shadcn/ui for UI development
- TypeScript for type safety
- Vercel for deployment 